Here are some key information about Palu and Donggala, on the island of Sulawesi:
Palu is the capital of the central province of Sulawesi, located at the end of a narrow gulf on the west coast of Sulawesi, with a population of about 379,800 in 2017.
The city celebrated 40 years of existence when it was hit by tsunami and earthquake.
Donggala is a regency that stretches on a coast with an area of more than 300 km in the northwest of Sulawesi Island.
